title: Co-Founder and CEO
location: San Francisco, California, United States of America
summary:
I’m currently building Fresco (YC F24) an AI copilot for construction superintendents. 

Previously, I was Chief of Staff and Director of Partnerships at January AI, a precision medicine company based in the Bay Area. I have my BA and MS from Brown, and I've also worked at NASA (SynBio), Human Capital (VC), and Vault Health (PM).

I enjoyed an exit from my political tech startup, DownBallot Solutions, in 2022. I also make investments in early-stage technology companies, with a focus on consumer software and digital health. I'm always happy to chat about science or entrepreneurship!

title: PHD Candidate
location: San Francisco, California, United States of America
summary:
I put my PhD on pause to co-found my startup AutoComputer (YC F24).

My profile highlights scientific and technical competencies I have accumulated in Braintech and AI over the last seven years as a researcher. As an academic, I received several prestigious awards to self-fund my research which resulted in three first-author scientific publications in those subjects, with more manuscripts in progress, and a provisional patent submitted. 

I have become a versatile communicator, leader, and problem-solver, who loves to learn new skills. BJJ hobbyist, competitive chess player (former), and recreational soccer player.

Personal website: http://ricksugden.weebly.com/
current_job_description: To assess the feasibility of using consumer-grade EEG wearables for remote medicine, I am conducting a pilot study for the monitoring of brain tumour patients. I developed and optimized the data-collection protocol as well as the automated machine learning analysis pipelines.

title: Content Creator
location: San Francisco, California, United States of America
summary:
I'm a medical doctor who graduated from Imperial College London, UK, where I also attended the Imperial College Business School and received a First Class Honours in Management. I moved to New York following my graduation and successfully matched into a Dermatology training program at the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai.

I'm hugely passionate about the overlap of healthcare and technology. I founded the MedTech Student Network during my time in medical school, completed a postdoctoral research fellowship in mobile health prior to starting residency training, and have recently been working on an AI-powered skincare assistant.

summary: I work on the foundations of machine learning, advised by Mikhail Belkin. I explore the potential AI & ML has to affect global change, as well as how we can make these algorithms more generally intelligent. • I am exploring the theoretical foundations of deep learning in Belkin Lab at HDSI, UCSD.

summary: I began programming in middle school with TI-Basic on my calculator, which led to automating most of my math homework and developing an appreciation for how computers and math work. Since then, I've used the same problem solving skills at companies of all stages and sizes, including Facebook pre-IPO where I was part of the 2nd intern class and later helping grow an 8 person startup to unicorn status. Nowadays, I'm working on my own thing which has been a challenging and rewarding experience. I view myself as a generalist and I thrive on technical challenges, building teams, and continuously learning all that I can. I'm happy to work on any part of the stack, be it frontend, backend, web, OS, people, or the occasional math problem. I'm also fond of music, the outdoors, and economics.

- Ethical considerations in medical AI, including algorithmic fairness and transparency

summary:
As a two-time Y Combinator alum, I thrive at the intersection of technology, innovation, and business strategy. With a strong track record of launching and scaling startups, I’m passionate about solving complex problems and building products that create real-world impact.

Throughout my entrepreneurial journey, I’ve honed expertise in artificial intelligence and machine learning, securities, product development, fundraising, and leadership. Whether it’s driving operational excellence or navigating the dynamic landscape of tech startups, my focus remains on delivering measurable value.

Looking ahead, I’m always eager to connect with like-minded innovators, investors, and leaders who share a passion for shaping the future of industries through transformative ideas.

title: Co-Founder, CTO
location: Berlin, Berlin, Germany
summary:
I am building Dexter, the AI process automation tool for field operations. We build state of the art AI agent workflows to automate your processes end-to-end.

At Dance, I worked on all aspects of our product: from consumer web products to internal tooling for our operations team. My work ranges from hands-on programming efforts to working closely with other leaders on long term planning and analysis. 

At Zalando, I led multiple teams in the Client Engineering group working on Zalando’s GraphQL API, media delivery, backed-driven native mobile UIs, core web frameworks, and tracking.

At SoundCloud, I led the Core Listener Experience group (20+ people) which include the Player, Media Streaming, and Core Listener teams.

The Player and Media Streaming teams handle petabytes of data, gigabytes per second of traffic, and strive to provide a blazing fast playback experience to our users.

The Core Listener team is responsible for core mobile and web features like the Library, and Offline Sync.

I've spoken at conferences on the topic of continuous integration, testing and delivering large cross functional projects.
current_job_description: Building Dexter, AI process automation for ops teams.

sub_title: AI Business & Strategy Expert I Public Speaker & Freelance Consultant I Founder AI Strategy Institute💡I University Lecturer to 1.000+ I Besides: Yoga teacher 🧘🏻‍♂️
summary:
Hey! 👋🏻
I'm Tristan, an AI strategist and lecturer with a passion for developing AI solutions and strategies for startups, multinational corporations and government institutions.

What I do:

♦️ Think Tank & Research: I provide in-depth research, write white papers, and offer expert opinions on AI in interviews, on stage, and in panels. My insights have been published in various news outlets such as Handelsblatt, FAZ, Forbes, ORF, etc.

♦️  Inspiration & Keynotes: I deliver engaging keynotes and talks on topics such as AI and GenAI, delivering real value with AI, AI for innovation, and building successful AI startups/products.

♦️  Upskilling & Training: I offer workshops and training sessions in AI, covering areas such as AI strategy, introduction to AI, AI use case ideation, AI project management, machine learning lifecycle management, and applied AI ethics. I also conduct university courses focused on AI management for both tech and non-tech audiences.

♦️  Consulting: I provide consulting services for AI strategy and related projects, including setting up AI strategies and roadmaps for startups, SMEs, and established public and private organizations. I also develop AI graduate talent programs and AI incubation programs.

♦️  Startup Support: As a startup advisor, venture builder, jury member, and investor, I support various AI-related startups and projects, including due diligence and other exciting initiatives.

My experience includes collaborations with GovTech Campus, Bitkom, Munich Tech Days, Austrian Parliament, City of Munich, Bavarian AI Agency, Campus Founders, AI Founders, Bosch, Ver.di, and many more.

📩 If you want to work with me, feel free to contact me via LinkedIn.

Have a great day & don't forget to smile! 😊



PS: Keep up to date with the future of AI on my blog: medium.com/@tristan.s.b.post.

summary:
I am an IIT Bombay student having currently passed my fourth year of the Dual Degree program in civil engineering department with specialization in transport and systems engineering.

I am a passionate individual who strives to learn through in hand experiences, hence in my pursuit of spreading my scope of knowledge in my early career, I have interned at various roles.

Currently being summer associate at PwC in Operations department, I am striving to develop my technical knowledge of vast operations in large scale industries and the process of optimizing the same using technology tools. Earlier I was interning with Reserve Bank of India in a finance and policy analysis role which was based on implementation of IBC on financial service providers. Before this I worked as an Intern at Ernst & Young in a sustainable strategy development role to reach India's COP 2030 goals. I have also worked with a social media startup called Slick! in the founder's office, which gave me a great experience of building growth strategies from scratch.

One of my peak experience involves serving Mood Indigo (the college cultural festival of IIT bombay) for two years, first as Concert's head to curate internationally renowned concerts, and thereafter as the Overall Coordinator where I carried the responsibility of overseeing every aspect of the fest while implementing widespread improvements.

Mindfully exploring new learning opportunities and at the same time trying to excel in each of them is the current life goal...
